Class AbstractStateIds

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hp.autonomy.aci.content.identifier.stateid.AbstractStateIds
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DocumentIdentifiers, IndexingIdentifiers, QueryIdentifiers, StateIds, Iterable<StateId>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StateId, StateIdsBuilder

    public abstract class AbstractStateIds
extends Object
implements StateIds
    An abstract base-class that partially implements the StateIds interface using sensible defaults.

      • toIndexingString

        public String toIndexingString()
        Description copied from interface: IndexingIdentifiers
        The string representation of this identifier, suitable for use as part of a DREREPLACE.

        Though the IndexingIdentifiers interface does not prescribe an implementation of the Object.toString() method, in practice it usually gives an ACI-ready version of the identifier. In most cases this will be the same as the indexing version but care should be taken to use the correct method as differences between the strings can cause subtly incorrect behaviour.

        Specified by:
        toIndexingString in interface IndexingIdentifiers
        Returns:
        A DREREPLACE identifier
